    "msg_9dc92a68bb51": {
      "content": "If you suspect the “auth/header or key loading” issue, the fastest way to pinpoint it is:\n\n1) **Check the actual error from your backend**\n- Are you getting **401** or **403**?\n- What is the exact error code/message in the response body (mask the key)?\n\n2) **Verify the key is present at runtime**\n- Log only whether it’s set (not the value), e.g.:\n  - `process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY ? \"set\" : \"missing\"`\n- In Docker/CI: confirm the env var is injected in the *runtime* container, not only build-time.\n\n3) **Verify the request header**\n- Must include exactly:\n  - `Authorization: Bearer <API_KEY>`\n- Ensure your code isn’t overwriting headers or skipping auth in some code path.\n\n4) **Confirm you’re not accidentally sending the key in the wrong place**\n- e.g., query params or `api_key` field instead of `Authorization`.\n\nPaste your **status code (401/403/etc.)** and the **error message/body** (with the key redacted), plus your backend language/framework (Node/Python/etc.), and I’ll tell you exactly which part is failing.",
      "created_at": "2026-05-31T06:37:34.800566+00:00",
      "id": "msg_9dc92a68bb51",
      "role": "assistant",
      "thread_id": "thread_cf87d4e814db"
    },
